Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:45.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ame agari no sora wo aogu tabi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.45,0:00:45.44,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I look up to \Nthe sky after the rain
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:51.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nakimushi datta koro no boku wo omou
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.52,0:00:51.15,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I think back to when I was a crybaby
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.19,0:00:58.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,dareka no senaka wo gamushara ni oikaketa
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.19,0:00:58.91,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I was chasing somebody's back blindly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.03,0:01:01.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"tsuyoku naritai" tte
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.03,0:01:01.70,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking "I want to be stronger"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:07.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ima wa kaze ni kieta "arigatou"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.79,0:01:07.21,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,The word "thank you" has \Nfaded into the wind now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.29,0:01:12.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,boku wa tsuyoku nareteiru no kana?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.29,0:01:12.38,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I getting stronger?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.51,0:01:18.05,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,kotae wa mada desou ni nai kara sa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.51,0:01:18.05,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the answer yet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:23.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,yappari mada aruiteiku yo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:23.39,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'll keep walking ahead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.64,0:01:25.81,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,saa yukou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.64,0:01:25.81,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.89,0:01:29.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,tachidomaru koto naku
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.89,0:01:29.11,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Without stopping
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.23,0:01:34.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nagareru toki ni makenai youni
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.23,0:01:34.44,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Without giving up to the flow of time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:39.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nando mo tachimukai tsuzukeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.49,0:01:39.91,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep getting back up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.05,0:01:45.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,taisetsu na mono ushinaitakunai kara
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.05,0:01:45.41,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I don't want to \Nlose something precious
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.54,0:01:50.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,boku no naka ni nagareru koe wa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.54,0:01:50.84,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,The voice inside of me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:56.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,zutto zutto boku wo sasaeteru
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:56.01,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,keeps sustaining me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.17,0:02:01.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,itazura na ame ga jama suru kedo
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.17,0:02:01.26,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Wicked rain will get in my way
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.39,0:02:06.10,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nigedasanai kara
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.39,0:02:06.10,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,But I won't walk away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:11.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,saa yukou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.52,0:02:11.69,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's go
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.81,0:02:14.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tachidomaru koto naku
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.81,0:02:14.98,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Without stopping
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:20.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nagareru toki ni makenai youni
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.11,0:02:20.16,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Without giving up to the flow of time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:25.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nando mo tachimukai tsuzukeyou
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:25.83,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep getting back up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:31.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,taisetsu na mono ushinaitakunai kara
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:31.38,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I don't want to \Nlose something precious
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.46,0:02:39.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,shinjita sono saki e to...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.46,0:02:39.68,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,To the future I believe in...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.85,0:02:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time is the Great Pirate Era.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.94,0:02:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Countless pirates fight \Ndesperately for the One Piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.13,0:02:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the great treasure left behind by \NGold Roger, King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.88,0:03:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monkey D. Luffy, a boy whose body turned \Nto rubber after he ate the Gum-Gum Fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,also takes to the sea to become \Nthe next King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.47,0:03:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As Luffy and his friends \Novercome numerous adventures,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.50,0:03:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the World Government is less and \Nless able to ignore their existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.46,0:03:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.88,0:03:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of adventure \Nis waiting for us next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.18,0:03:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The crew, on its way to the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.31,0:03:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will speed along the Grand Line again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.50,0:03:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Separated from the rest of the Straw Hats,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy made a raid on the Navy HQ to rescue \Nhis brother, Ace who was to be executed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.50,0:03:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, both Ace and \NWhitebeard lost their lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whitebeard, Ace...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.10,0:03:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us handle the burial of those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.42,0:03:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only because it's you, I \Nallow it, "Red-Haired"!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.88,0:04:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.90,0:04:03.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take the blame on myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.88,0:04:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.50,0:04:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treat the injured now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.73,0:04:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This war is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.02,0:04:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...over!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.33,0:04:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Mighty Leaders Face Each Other \NDown! Heralding the 'New Era'!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.86,0:04:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with it? I can't hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.50,0:04:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because of a bad connection?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.36,0:05:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened in the war after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.36,0:05:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did the Navy win?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.36,0:05:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--They did, didn't they?\N--It's getting clearer now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.73,0:05:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The Whitebeards have lost?\N--Did the Navy really win?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.00,0:05:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding the war occurring at Marineford
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.41,0:05:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,being waged by the Whitebeards \Nand we, the Navy HQ,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.90,0:05:24.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the process took longer than anticipated \Nbecause of the enemy's persistence
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.16,0:05:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Navy soldiers all \Nfought with a sense of justice
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.80,0:05:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and defeated all the \NWhitebeards and their allies
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.93,0:05:38.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and now we are happy to tell you that \Nthe Navy HQ gained a complete victory...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Navy is invincible! \NPraise all our heroes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.79,0:06:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be called to \Nduty at the HQ someday!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The war is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:14.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary pirate - Whitebeard lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.69,0:06:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The war is over, right?\N--Yes! You're safe now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.20,0:06:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--This is so great!\N--They did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.03,0:06:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.37,0:06:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurrah for the Navy! Hurray \Nfor the World Government!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.78,0:06:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And for victory and justice \Nand peace! Hurrah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the scene of the war - Marineford! \NThere are 7 ships out at sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:07:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those who would take part in the new era...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.64,0:07:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are there to witness this \Ngreat turning point in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.69,0:07:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Staring at the dust of the battle \Nrising above Marineford -
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,evidence of the workings of \Njustice in the Great Pirate Era -
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they sense the restlessness \Nof the changing of the times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain Drake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.95,0:07:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Finally... it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.71,0:07:25.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Navy has to change, also.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In no time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.13,0:07:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whitebeard's territory will sink in \Na sea of blood in this whirlpool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.51,0:07:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackbeard is the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.43,0:07:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has gained new followers \Nand Whitebeard's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.89,0:07:46.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they're gonna reign for while!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.11,0:07:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all... his fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll track him down soon enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:07:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! To the New World!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:03.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.59,0:08:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Apoo-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.21,0:08:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy will become his enemy. \NIs he really gonna save him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.38,0:08:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.30,0:08:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about Trafalgar Law. \NHe's known for his brutality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.72,0:08:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't save Straw Hat Luffy \Nif there wasn't some catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.08,0:08:27.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.69,0:08:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Captain Hawkins?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been trying to see the \Nodds that Luffy's still alive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it never reaches zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.12,0:08:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I was scared \Nwhen the war started,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now the great pirate, \NWhitebeard, is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.41,0:08:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's really over, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.16,0:08:51.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:09:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's over?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.50,0:09:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The new force who emerged during this \Nwar--that Blackbeard is quite a guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.23,0:09:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The New World is ruled by The Four Emperors.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.61,0:09:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whitebeard, "Red-Haired", Kaido, Big Mam.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since one of them is dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.12,0:09:26.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the World is out of balance and no \None can predict the consequences!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.08,0:09:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the beginning of a new era the \Nlikes of which no one has ever seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The news of the Navy's victory \Nin the war at Marineford,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.89,0:09:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the biggest war since the beginning \Nof the Great Pirate Era,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.73,0:09:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,spread all over the world \Nin the blink of an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.22,0:09:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and people are celebrating \Nthe news everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:09:56.70,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,East Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.99,0:09:57.99,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,EAST BLUE
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.70,0:09:57.99,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurrah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.99,0:10:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Whitebeard is dead!\N--Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.08,0:10:05.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--We're safe now!\N--I'm so glad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.58,0:10:07.47,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,West Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.58,0:10:08.25,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,WEST BLUE
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.25,0:10:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea will be in peace now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.38,0:10:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurrah!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:14.67,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,South Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.96,0:10:15.63,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,SOUTH BLUE
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.67,0:10:16.30,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna have a bargain sale today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.30,0:10:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So are we!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.09,0:10:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The Navy has won!\N--I'm so relieved!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:23.43,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,North Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.47,0:10:24.18,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,NORTH BLUE
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.86,0:10:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Let's drink, everybody!\N--We have tons of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:33.15,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:34.27,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,GRAND LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:35.16,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.16,0:10:36.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna play tag!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.53,0:10:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hide and seek!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.95,0:10:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.72,0:10:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like most of history, some facts are \Ntrimmed off as the news goes around
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.88,0:10:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and just the two words \N"Navy victory" stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.59,0:11:01.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The people, in their excitement at the \Nnews, failed to notice something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.08,0:11:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.14,0:11:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you people! That's hilarious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whitebeard said that the great \Ntreasure - One Piece is real!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.55,0:11:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.32,0:11:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is so much more out \Nthere! Let's set sail!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.69,0:11:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Navy victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.71,0:11:39.51,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,The result is not necessarily peace...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.96,0:11:36.96,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,NEW WORLD: FOODVALTEN ISLAND
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You can't come any further! \NDon't come into our town!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.93,0:11:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the loss of a deterrent - \Nnamely, the threat of Whitebeard -
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the world of the seas has \Nbecome very unsettled...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.59,0:12:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Admiral Sengoku!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:24.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.55,0:12:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've had word from Impel Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.22,0:12:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Magellan alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.31,0:12:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got beaten badly and is barely alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.24,0:12:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's been treated intensively \Nby the medical team.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:41.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a dutiful man - he's blaming himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.11,0:12:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said that if he could \Nmove now, he'd kill himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.20,0:12:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him do such stupid thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.62,0:12:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What has been going on at the prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.46,0:12:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to tell you the \Ncondition as it stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:13:01.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The situation on level 6 is especially \Nbad. It's literally a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.09,0:13:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A disaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:09.76,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,UNDERWATER PRISON IMPEL DOWN
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.77,0:13:25.28,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,LEVEL 6
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.44,0:13:22.47,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.47,0:13:27.00,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,You prisoners're doomed to \Nbe stuck behind bars forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.74,0:13:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got nothing to do except wait to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about this?! Why don't \Nyou fight each other in the cell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.02,0:13:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will free those of you who \Nsurvive as members of my crew!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.67,0:13:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really?!\N--Get me out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:47.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me be your crew member!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:14:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he has freed selected members from \Nthe worst criminals in the world?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.96,0:14:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But only 4 prisoners were taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.00,0:14:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,San Juan Wolf, Avalo Pizarro, \NVasco Shot, Catarina Devon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are obviously more \Nprisoners missing from level 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.72,0:14:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Then, there are \Nmore escapees from level 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.51,0:14:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If even one of the prisoners from level \N6 sneaks into a country somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.23,0:14:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the people will be in grave danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.48,0:14:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Check to see how many there were.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get their names, and put a \Nmost wanted list out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.41,0:14:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.58,0:14:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm under orders from the World Government
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.88,0:15:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nto keep this level 6 matter secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More blunders will harm the \NGovernment's reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.22,0:15:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn them!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.56,0:16:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.10,0:16:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doflamingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:10.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moria, you're too weak to go \Non with the title as a Warlord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.99,0:16:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Died in the War of the \NBest" sounds better...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.28,0:16:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...than "done in by the Government".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.76,0:16:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whose idea was this?! Sengoku?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.82,0:16:27.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, someone much higher up the ladder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.76,0:16:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hot... Too hot...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.39,0:16:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it so hot? I can't take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you shut up already?! \NYou're making me feel hot too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.57,0:16:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're hairy. I don't blame you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.15,0:16:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like it when we submerge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.89,0:16:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to stay in such a cramped place...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.97,0:16:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...with messy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.53,0:17:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the messiest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't take it! I have no choice but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.90,0:17:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--...to make you feel the same!\N--Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.21,0:17:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--You're so hot!\N--That's gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.71,0:17:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.72,0:17:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg you! A little bit is fine! \NLet me get some fresh air!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Now, stop rubbing your sweat on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surface! Let's surface now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.99,0:17:46.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so refreshing! How nice it is outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.50,0:17:49.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm cool! Right side - okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.54,0:17:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Left side - okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:54.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Front...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.09,0:17:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Snake - okay! Snake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.05,0:17:59.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What the hell?!\N--How did a snake get here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.23,0:18:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Navy ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.81,0:18:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Tell Captain!\N--Someone's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Warlord - the Pirate Empress, Boa Hancock!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I turned all \Nthe Navy soldiers to stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So how is Luffy doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.36,0:18:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it bad? He'll recover, won't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know that we \Nwere gonna surface here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.97,0:18:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was scared thinking that the \NNavy was still chasing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.35,0:18:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made Salome follow you underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.43,0:18:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I see!\N--Don't change the subject, you fuzzy beast!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.83,0:18:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I'm sorry!\N--So weak!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.02,0:18:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is Luffy doing? Tell me now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:57.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.15,0:19:01.11,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,THE HEART PIRATES â€“ CAPTAIN TRAFALGAR LAW
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:01.11,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I did everything I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:03.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, he's okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.83,0:19:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to stabilize him. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...he took greater damage than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.39,0:19:15.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no guarantee \Nthat he will survive yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.42,0:19:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no wonder!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.55,0:19:23.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.04,0:19:28.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Straw boy couldn't even \Nstand up at Impel Down once!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.40,0:19:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Straw Hat was risking his life!\N--We got out of the prison thanks to him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:36.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of him, we can \Nmake our dream come true:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.12,0:19:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To go to the Kamabakka Kingdom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.65,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To the New Kamas' home from New Kama Land!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.11,0:19:47.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.93,0:19:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are prisoners of Impel Down. \NLooks like they're Luffy's friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.44,0:19:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have snuck into the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.18,0:19:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe that he \Npushed himself that hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how much he wanted \Nto save his brother Ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.47,0:20:08.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! We know how much \Nhe pushed himself to do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.77,0:20:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that brother died in front of his eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.42,0:20:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in order to protect him...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.24,0:20:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no justice in this world! It's \Nnot surprising that he broke down!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.95,0:20:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it all! Hang in there, Straw Hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.45,0:20:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got to live! You got to, Straw Hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.27,0:20:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a tragedy! I wish \NI could take his place!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.39,0:20:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poor Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm jealous...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.28,0:20:52.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be nice to have the Pirate \NEmpress care about you that much...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.23,0:20:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, are you a friend of Straw boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:20:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't have to save him at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.19,0:21:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're wondering about my motivation, \NI can come up with a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.90,0:21:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's okay. Sometimes your \Ninstinct tells you what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.12,0:21:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey, wait!\N--You can't walk around yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.83,0:21:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Don't push yourself like that!\N--He told you to rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.01,0:21:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--The wound could open up!\N--Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.55,0:21:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jimbei!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.93,0:21:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Trafalgar Law from \Nthe North Blue, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.18,0:21:32.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.39,0:21:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, is it okay for you \Nto move around like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.31,0:21:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.44,0:21:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saved my life!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.98,0:21:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must rest. It could kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.65,0:21:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't ease my mind. It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.53,0:21:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I have just lost \Nwas too important to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why I know that Luffy-kun \Nmust be going through far worse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.83,0:22:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least, his instinct to protect himself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.88,0:22:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,forced him to lose \Nconsciousness at that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he survives,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.96,0:22:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't stop worrying about \Nthe moment that he wakes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.01,0:22:21.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, fuzzy beast, do you \Nhave a Transponder Snail?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.19,0:22:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... I mean... yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.35,0:22:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.40,0:22:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I'm jealous. He's like her servant...\N--Yeah, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.39,0:22:33.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna call the Kuja's ship so we can go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.28,0:22:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\Nacross the Calm Belt even with this submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.33,0:22:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the Government finds out that Luffy's \Nalive, they're gonna come after him!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.97,0:22:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us harbor him at the Maiden Island!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.21,0:22:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.21,0:22:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they still see me as a \NWarlord, Luffy can rest safely!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.82,0:23:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.44,0:23:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At Hancock's suggestion,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.73,0:23:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy is taken to Maiden Island \Nso his wounds can heal,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.05,0:23:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there he finally regains consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.80,0:23:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But as his memories of the battle return,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.15,0:23:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy is overtaken by deep despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.81,0:23:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the net episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.21,0:23:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Landing at the Maiden Island! \NThe Harsh Reality Falls upon Luffy!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
